QUALIFICATION: this species has been widely known as Psaltoda argentata (Germar). However, the name argentata cannot be applied to this species as it is preoccupied by Cicadetta argentata (Olivier, 1790), the name of a European species, both species being originally called Cicada argentata. The next available name for P. argentata is plaga Walker, and this should therefore be used (Moulds, 1990)
